Python<pre><code>@invoker.entry_point
def run(
    target: sierra.Param[
        str | None,  # Type annotation
        sierra.SierraOption(mandatory="MANDATORY")  # Validation rule
    ]
):
    if target is None:  # Won't happen - Sierra validates!
        return sierra.create_error_result("Missing target")
    # target is guaranteed to be a string
</code></pre> <p>Benefits:</p> <ul> <li>✅ Catch errors early - Before script runs</li> <li>✅ Auto-generate help - CLI knows parameter types</li> <li>✅ Better IDE support - Autocomplete works</li> <li>✅ Self-documenting - Code explains itself</li> </ul>

